From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 03:49:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] drm/nouveau/instmem: use WC-optimized copy for suspend

Nouveau saves every preserved instance-memory object to system memory
before suspending the GPU.  On NV50 and later, mapped objects are read
through a write-combined BAR2 mapping.  Ordinary memcpy_fromio() reads
from WC mappings are extremely slow on x86 because they do not prefetch.

Use drm_memcpy_from_wc(), which uses MOVNTDQA where available and falls
back to the existing copy semantics on other platforms.  Keep the BAR0
slow path, BAR2 teardown ordering, and resume path unchanged.

On a GT216M, a Plasma session had 31.824 MiB in 82 mapped objects.  The
old path copied them at 1.902 MiB/s and added 16.729 seconds to every
suspend.  The machine is a bare-metal SSE4.1-capable x86 system, so it can
use the optimized path.

Signed-off-by: Codex <codex@openai.com>
---
 .../drm/nouveau/nvkm/subdev/instmem/base.c    | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/subdev/instmem/base.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/subdev/instmem/base.c
index 6b9ed61684a0..a0ebca9d44aa 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/subdev/instmem/base.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/subdev/instmem/base.c
@@ -23,6 +23,10 @@
  */
 #include "priv.h"
 
+#include <linux/iosys-map.h>
+
+#include <drm/drm_cache.h>
+
 #include <subdev/bar.h>
 
 /******************************************************************************
@@ -64,7 +68,10 @@ nvkm_instobj_save(struct nvkm_instobj *iobj)
 		for (i = 0; i < size; i += 4)
 			iobj->suspend[i / 4] = nvkm_ro32(memory, i);
 	} else {
-		memcpy_fromio(iobj->suspend, map, size);
+		struct iosys_map dst = IOSYS_MAP_INIT_VADDR(iobj->suspend);
+		struct iosys_map src = IOSYS_MAP_INIT_VADDR_IOMEM(map);
+
+		drm_memcpy_from_wc(&dst, &src, size);
 	}
 	nvkm_done(memory);
 	return 0;
-- 
2.53.0
